<subSubSection id="6CDEA892D63F949D2E6446244AD61329" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph id="8110DEBE2E5AB77423E056C05BF97D0F" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="30CC79FD477ADF00BA3C12963716DBC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
Morphometric data for type specimens given in Table 
<tableCitation id="F3FD9596A26728ACC7A35B88110091A4" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphometry of Gobiobotia lii. Measurements are in percentage of standard length, except for standard length (SL). SD, standard deviation; r, Pearson's correlation coefficient; p, significance; linear regression parameters calculated from measurements. HT = Holotype." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/57DF2A88722BCF2514CAB82D131FE807" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" tableUuid="57DF2A88722BCF2514CAB82D131FE807">1</tableCitation>
. General body appearance of holotype shown in Figs 
<figureCitation id="9142ADF1E2FE230D3CDE8E405CA0EA16" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Gobiobotia lii, holotype, IHB 202103051401, 48.6 mm SL, photographed alive immediately upon capture. P. R. China: Hubei Province: Qichun County: Xiangqiao Town: Chang-Jiang Basin, Qi-Shui." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80547.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665282" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">1</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="191073D787E769385634DF52F4BB1FF2" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Dorsal (a), lateral (b) and ventral (c) views of Gobiobotia lii, holotype, IHB 202103051401, 48.6 mm SL. P. R. China: Hubei Province: Qichun County: Xiangqiao Town: Chang-Jiang Basin, Qi-Shui." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80547.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665283" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">2</figureCitation>
. Body small and slender, with maximum depth at dorsal-fin origin. Pre-dorsal body profile depressed. Ventral profile slightly compressed. Abdomen flat or slightly convex from pectoral-fin insertion to anal-fin origin and slightly concave from anal-fin origin to caudal-fin base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5DAE65C0C56FF454604830E082A2DE36" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Head depressed and broad. Snout pointed in lateral view and slightly bluntly rounded in dorsal view, longer than post-orbital head. Eyes small and dorsolateral; diameter less than interorbital width. Interorbital space flattened. Some irregular papillae present on the mental region.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BFCA2667E329CE1A44E8519F8AA88844" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Mouth inferior, with opening laterally extending to the vertical line of front edge of nostril. Four pairs of barbels: one pair of maxillary barbels and three pairs of mental barbels. Maxillary barbels extending closely to a vertical line through middle of eye; first pair of mental barbels short, inserted at the same level passing through maxillary-barbel roots and anterior to roots of second mental barbels and reaching anterior margin of eye; second pair of mental barbels extending beyond bases of third pair of mental barbels to hind margin of pre-opercula; third pair of mental barbels long, reaching pectoral-fin insertion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="81F2751B00599E56D21017450F681A5C" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Fins rays flexible, dorsal fin with 3 simple and 7 (14 specimens examined) branched rays; pectoral fin with 1 simple and 12 (6) or 13 (8) branched rays, extending about two-thirds of the distance to pelvic-fin insertion. Pelvic fin with 1 simple and 7 (14) branched rays, reaching beyond the midway to anal-fin origin and surpassing anus; inserted closer to anal-fin origin than to anterior end of pectoral-fin base; located opposite to that of dorsal-fin base. Anal fin with 3 simple and 6 (14) branched rays; origin equidistant from pelvic-fin insertion and caudal-fin base. Anus positioned closer to the pelvic-fin insertion than to anal-fin origin. Caudal fin moderately forked; lower lobes are longer than upper lobes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="372E018DEF4A04BBF3B42FD40D321E3D" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
Lateral line complete and almost straight, extending along mid-lateral of body, with 37 (7) or 38 (7) pored scales; scale rows above and below lateral lines 5 and 3; circumpeduncular scales 11 (7) or 12 (7) and pre-dorsal mid-line scales 13 (14). Body covered with moderately-sized scales; no scales on breast and belly in front of vent. Vertebral counts 4+31-32 (modally 4+32, see Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4B7B1217EC15CF7FE6F9D643272C031E" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Micro-CT images of lateral body in: (a) G. lii, IHB 202103051401, holotype and (b) G. jiangxiensis, IHB 90 IV 1256, holotype. X-rayed photographs of lateral body in: (c) G. pappenheimi, ZMB 18466, holotype and (d) G. nicholsi, AMNH 20523, holotype." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80547.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665285" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="66BCDFD602B332D399313D85602AE591" doi="10.3897/zse.98.80547.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665285" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="16ED18A64F76E6A2C3F5D076C002235C" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="E974EEEC65BBDE54BA62C4C8BC1AB1FA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Figure 4.</emphasis>
Micro-CT images of lateral body in: (
<emphasis id="761320B08CEF0D4DD238A72AE4FAE859" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">a</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName id="630B1D04AA1D33F33161B13D1E29ACB6" genus="G." lsidName="G. lii" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="lii">
<emphasis id="B7DC2E5738579272BD200DB02EAA9DB6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">G. lii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, IHB 202103051401, holotype and (
<emphasis id="A31C6DED2E11CD0C68B4FBE93567DA3C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">b</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName id="65998A9B61BB8C1711A2C01B3950E4EF" genus="G." lsidName="G. jiangxiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="jiangxiensis">
<emphasis id="284D085D8084A3844433D7EF3A40621C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">G. jiangxiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, IHB 90IV1256, holotype. X-rayed photographs of lateral body in: (
<emphasis id="6151EF23B8EB25FC052AE2BD27343851" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">c</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName id="94FFCA44BCC122B3A86630DC75BE7734" genus="G." lsidName="G. pappenheimi" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="pappenheimi">
<emphasis id="9D71A8BCFF2C3882EBCDDE58DDEB47B7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">G. pappenheimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ZMB 18466, holotype and (
<emphasis id="29A74F1D234F4799E6DE14F727B8E862" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">d</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName id="75BC12E408597F5B5DBD5F2C47E68BB2" genus="G." lsidName="G. nicholsi" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="nicholsi">
<emphasis id="808558E1CCFB6DD3C151E33C32CC2B5E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">G. nicholsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, AMNH 20523, holotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DE31F6C98BA38ED5DC64E8D46303438B" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="colouration">
<paragraph id="8569D9BB30DFB413363A9242519911AE" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Colouration.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96E5634FFF4F095D66DBD6E2AE5A41FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">In freshly-collected specimens, head and dorsum of body golden yellow, underside and abdomen golden grey; back and lateral head peppered with dark flecks. Back darker and belly lighter, with a dark spot back of the head, 12-13 dorsal dark brown spots extending along mid-line of dorsum from nape to caudal-fin base and 9-10 large dark brown spots along middle of side from gill opening to caudal-fin base. Fin golden yellow, distal margin hyaline.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="561EB498216312C00CBE80881E34CE66" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
In formalin-stored specimens, ground colour slightly faded; body dorsally greyish and ventrally greyish-white; dorsal and lateral dark brown spots not clear and the back of the head becoming yellowish-brown. Dorsal, pectoral, pelvic and anal fins light greyish; caudal fin with numerous narrow dark crossbars (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="47421D1B8A93F3F6C2FE1FAACECFFC3B" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Dorsal (a), lateral (b) and ventral (c) views of Gobiobotia lii, holotype, IHB 202103051401, 48.6 mm SL. P. R. China: Hubei Province: Qichun County: Xiangqiao Town: Chang-Jiang Basin, Qi-Shui." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80547.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665283" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ABA2F9CBA6263A644918AF6484467975" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="sexual dimorphism">
<paragraph id="ED381906AEFB37561126EC3B63EEDB96" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Sexual dimorphism.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5596054A688743C8B517E0E94586E3E0" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">No sexual dimorphism was observed in the specimens examined.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6F155A905786644A19B7DD76C5BC028" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="201A481B64B09A989BD649186A357A9E" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE927746718D6A81A51156029623EE3E" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName id="2F595B34B680856E38CFBB648D5A56AD" authorityName="Chen &amp; Wang &amp; Cao &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" class="Pisces" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Gobiobotia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gobiobotia lii" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lii">
<emphasis id="141A726060A79D8125EABCBDF171E0D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Gobiobotia lii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the Qi-Shui, a stream tributary to the middle Chang-Jiang mainstem at Qichun County, Hubei (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2C59FD23AA36B2CF48E84AC964CF7FAE" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Map showing the distribution of type series of Gobiobotia lii in the middle Chang-Jiang Basin." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80547.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665286" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">5</figureCitation>
). The new species was found in turbid, slow-running water with mixed substrates including sand and gravel (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9752DEA2EC15F08FB750F1225DE38F35" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Sampling locality of the holotype (IHB 202103051401) of Gobiobotia lii in the Qi-Shui stream, tributary to the middle Chang-Jiang mainstem in Xiangqiao Town, Qichun County, 5 March 2021." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.98.80547.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665287" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">6</figureCitation>
); and Lake Dongting in Hunan, where it was collected in lotic habitats or estuaries of effluents. Co-existing species included 
<taxonomicName id="4024D378D0EC770A7F99EBF8E482C7F0" baseAuthorityName="Cantor" baseAuthorityYear="1842" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Misgurnus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Misgurnus anguillicaudatus" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anguillicaudatus">
<emphasis id="D5B076E285C817E15408F4D0114F23EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Misgurnus anguillicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C74ABDC954470FB3CEE23B44236C0E13" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1873" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Opsariichthys" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opsariichthys bidens" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis id="EAB6D120A66148B6535B99ACC59FA0C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Opsariichthys bidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E71BE7D70706D1B99124D6ED861BB64C" authorityName="Dabry de Thiersant" authorityYear="1872" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Parabotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parabotia fasciata" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis id="110E01246337D202D1CE5FFDF49B94B2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Parabotia fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="16539E6B069A640C7E3EBDA86015F5C2" doi="10.3897/zse.98.80547.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665286" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph id="36BAC78902804474864FC5B0AA8EB9C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="B56300A4982215D955B2F6C3C86626A1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Figure 5.</emphasis>
Map showing the distribution of type series of 
<taxonomicName id="2B62AD136F04428BE8D50CE237C59828" authorityName="Chen &amp; Wang &amp; Cao &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" class="Pisces" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Gobiobotia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gobiobotia lii" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lii">
<emphasis id="9F93996366679E379312C97519E89688" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Gobiobotia lii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the middle Chang-Jiang Basin.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="757B4E27F7103997F7AE84F5ACA385CB" doi="10.3897/zse.98.80547.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665287" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
<paragraph id="7C2FBB0EFAF210402B628D7053BC9EF9" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
